      "writtenOn": "2019-02-07T19:41:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking at this again, I think no change is needed. Although, I would favor a style change.\n\nMy original concern is I thought we weren\u0027t clearing out all of the contents. But I see now that we memset() each subarray. So we are clearing it.\n\nHowever, memset() always feels a tad dangerous to me.\nWhat do you all think about using std::fill()? And while we\u0027re at it, we could also use std::array.\n\nThose could happen in a separate patch. I\u0027m happy to do that if you all like the idea.",
      "parentUuid": "86377741_c6689f05",
