      "writtenOn": "2019-02-07T19:45:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s pretty idiomatic in Skia to use memset() / memcpy(), or really here sk_bzero(), but I don\u0027t think anyone will mind if you want to switch places that make sense to std::fill, std::copy, etc.  I can\u0027t imagine it ends up any different when compiling with optimization.\n\n(We do use memset() / memcpy() in some situations to operate on raw bytes or do things like bit-casts that you just can\u0027t do with strongly-typed std::fill / std::copy.  So I don\u0027t think we can replace _everything_.)",
